        <body>
            <p>.cookies are small text files that website send to a users browser to store information about the users visit.</p>
                <p>.They are an eesential part of the morden making websites more user-friendly and personalizing the users online experience.</p>
                    <p><h2>USES OF COOKIES</P></h>
                        <p>.Improving performance</p>
                            <p>personalizing content</p>
                                <p>.Improving navigation<p>
                                <p>Tailoring advertising</p>
                                <p>Detecting spam and fraud</p>
                                <h1>TYPES OF COOKIES</h1>
                                <p><b>Sessioncookies</p></b>
                                <p>.Temporary cookies that remain in your browsers cookie file until you leave the website.</p>
                                <P><b>Persistent cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.Aslo known as authentication cookies ,these cookies remain in your browsers cookie file for a longer peroid of time.</p>
                                    <p><b>First-party cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.set directly by the website  your are visiting ,these cookies are used to remember user perferences loke login details or language settings.</p>
                                    <p><b>Thrid-party cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.Created by a website you are not visiting ,these cookies are usually created by advertisers.</p>
                                    <p><b>Magic cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.Uniquie identifiers sent from a server to a users computer,these cookies were more common in older computer systems.</p>
                                    <p><b>Super cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.Originate from a top-leveln domain ,such as .com.</p>
                                    <p><b>Zombie cookies</p></b>
                                    <p>.Atype of flash cookie that can regenrate themselves after being deleted.</P>
